TS GALAXY earned a hard-fought 1-0 victory over Swallows FC in a relegation battle at Dobsonville Stadium on Saturday evening. Augustine Kwem scored the only goal of the match in the 35th minute of the game to boost their survival hopes in what has been a rollercoaster season for them. The three points saw Galaxy moving from the foot of the log to position 14, with 16 points gathered from 18 matches. On the flip side, Swallows are in position 15. They are a point behind Galaxy as they have 15 from 20 matches. Baroka FC, who are playing Sekhukhune United on Sunday, are now at the bottom of the log with 14 points from 18 games. It was a highly contested clash between the two sides as they both needed maximum points. This was Galaxy's first away win, and they did it in style, keeping their first clean sheet which was their third this season. Galaxy started on a high in the second half of the match, putting Swallows under pressure, but they could not extend their lead. The visitor were reduced to 10 men in the 69th minute, Ebrahim Seedat got a second yellow card for a foul on Khethukuthula Ndlovu. However, Swallows failed to capitalize on that as they could not break Galaxy defence. Galaxy captain led by example and was voted man-of-the-match. Talking after the match, Snoka said: "I think this game will determine our way going forward. We came here knowing how important it was to get three points. Our aim was to grind all the points, even if it meant we played creepy football and were able to do that. "After going one man down, we knew that they would come to us. But everyone did well. We are happy with the three points." With 10 games to go for Swallows, there is immense pressure on Swallows, and they coach Kerr to collect points to be safe from relegation.